<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="47" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="47">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Montesinos" authorityYear="2020" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Drymaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Drymaria veliziae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="veliziae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Drymaria veliziae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. auriculipetala" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" rank="species" species="auriculipetala">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">D. auriculipetala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Mattf. from which it differs in having glands covering the stems and pedicels, leaves with elliptic-ovate form, shorter in size (4-5.5 mm vs. 5-15 mm in 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. auriculipetala" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" rank="species" species="auriculipetala">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">D. auriculipetala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), by the leaves arranged in fascicules (vs. simple opposite leaves), stipules in numbers of 14-20 per axis (vs. 2-4 in 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. auriculipetala" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" rank="species" species="auriculipetala">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">D. auriculipetala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), pedicel size (1-2 mm long vs. 5-40 mm) and by the capsule size being smaller (1.4-1.6 mm vs. 3-4 mm).
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/phytokeys.140.47738.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/382681" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" start="Figure 1" startId="F1">
